HEADWORD: Ritornello
<hw>Ri`tor*nel"lo</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>ritornello</ets>,
dim. of <ets>ritorno</ets> return, fr. <ets>ritornare</ets> to return:
cf. F. <ets>ritournelle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A short return or repetition; a concluding symphony to an air,
often consisting of the burden of the song.</def> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
short intermediate symphony, or instrumental passage, in the course of a
vocal piece; an interlude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

